---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Plugin Authoring" description="Write a TaskAdapter or VcsAdapter for substrate.">
  <h1>Plugin Authoring</h1>
  <p>
    Substrate has two plugin axes today (v0.8): <strong>TaskAdapter</strong>
    (task tracker integration — Linear / Jira / GitHub Issues / your own)
    and <strong>VcsAdapter</strong> (VCS interaction; default is the built-in
    git adapter). Both are loaded via dynamic <code>import()</code> based on
    the npm package name listed in <code>substrate.config.json</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>The TaskAdapter contract</h2>

  <p>An adapter is an object satisfying:</p>

  <pre><code>{`interface TaskAdapter {
  readonly name: string;
  readonly version: string;
  findTask(input: { id: string }): Promise<SubstrateTask | null>;
  searchTasks(input: { query: string; limit?: number }): Promise<SubstrateTask[]>;
  createTask(input: CreateTaskInput): Promise<SubstrateTask>;
  updateTask(input: UpdateTaskInput): Promise<SubstrateTask>;
  completeTask(input: { id: string; actualHours?: number }): Promise<SubstrateTask>;
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>
    The interface is checked at load time by <code>isTaskAdapter()</code> — a
    structural-typing guard. <strong>You do not need to import from
    substrate.</strong> Adapter packages duplicate the interface inline (see
    <code>@op4z/substrate-adapter-stub</code> for the reference shape).
  </p>

  <h2>Three reference adapters</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong><code>@op4z/substrate-adapter-stub</code></strong> — logs verbs to stderr, returns synthetic tasks. The contract checker and copy-paste template.</li>
    <li><strong><code>@op4z/substrate-adapter-linear</code></strong> — Linear via @linear/sdk.</li>
    <li><strong><code>@op4z/substrate-adapter-jira</code></strong> — Jira (Cloud or Server) via jira-client.</li>
    <li><strong><code>@op4z/substrate-adapter-github</code></strong> — GitHub Issues via Octokit.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Configuring</h2>

  <pre><code>{`{
  "extensions": {
    "taskAdapter": "@op4z/substrate-adapter-linear",
    "vcsAdapter": null
  }
}`}</code></pre>

  <p>
    Set the corresponding environment variable for credentials
    (<code>LINEAR_API_KEY</code>, <code>JIRA_API_TOKEN</code>, etc. — see
    each adapter's README).
  </p>

  <h2>Writing your own</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Create a new npm package with <code>substrate task</code> verbs.</li>
    <li>Implement the five methods. Return <code>SubstrateTask</code> shapes (id, title, description, status, priority, type, assignee, labels, estimatedHours, actualHours, url).</li>
    <li>Export as default. Substrate's loader imports the default and runs <code>isTaskAdapter()</code>.</li>
    <li>Test with a fake client; see the three reference adapter test files for the pattern (inject a narrow client-like interface, never hit real APIs in unit tests).</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>The VcsAdapter contract</h2>

  <p>
    Five verbs (getStatus, getBranch, getRemote, getDiff, commit). Built-in
    git adapter at <code>src/adapters/git.ts</code> uses <code>spawnSync('git',
    ...)</code>. A mercurial adapter would follow the same pattern.
  </p>
</Base>
